========================================================================
 QuantumForge v2.0.0 - Advanced GUI for Quantum ESPRESSO
========================================================================

 QuantumForge (formerly QUANTUMFORGE) is a comprehensive Graphical User Interface
 for Quantum ESPRESSO 7.5, thermo_pw 2.1.1, and related computational
 materials science software packages.

 Copyright (C) 2025 QuantumForge Team
 Originally developed by Satomichi Nishihara (QUANTUMFORGE v1.3, 2016-2018)

========================================================================
 KEY FEATURES
========================================================================

 - Full GUI for Quantum ESPRESSO 7.5 calculations
 - Support for pw.x, ph.x, dos.x, projwfc.x, bands.x, neb.x, pp.x
 - Thermodynamic calculations via thermo_pw 2.1.1
 - Phonon analysis with phonopy integration
 - Transport properties with BoltzTraP2 plugin
 - 3D atomic structure viewer and editor
 - Crystal structure building (surface, molecule, polymer)
 - Materials Project + PubChem database integration
 - SSH remote execution with PBS/SLURM/PJM job scheduler support
 - Space group detection and symmetry analysis
 - GNN force field interface (M3GNet, CHGNet, OCP)
 - Results visualization (band structure, DOS, phonon dispersion)

========================================================================
 SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS
========================================================================

 - Java Runtime Environment 11 or later (recommended: 17+)
 - Quantum ESPRESSO 7.5 (recommended)
 - thermo_pw 2.1.1 (optional, for thermodynamic calculations)
 - phonopy 2.30+ (optional, for phonon analysis)
 - BoltzTraP2 24.1+ (optional, for transport properties)

========================================================================
 SUPPORTED SOFTWARE
========================================================================

 - Quantum ESPRESSO v7.5 (primary engine)
 - thermo_pw v2.1.1 (thermodynamic properties)
 - phonopy v2.30+ (phonon band structures)
 - BoltzTraP2 v24.1+ (transport properties)
 - seekpath v2.1+ (band path generation)
 - spglib v2.10+ (space group detection)
 - xcrysden v1.6+ (visualization)

========================================================================
 INSTALLATION
========================================================================

 1. Install Quantum ESPRESSO 7.5 from https://www.quantum-espresso.org
 2. Install Java 11+ runtime
 3. Set QE paths in QuantumForge preferences
 4. (Optional) Install thermo_pw, phonopy, BoltzTraP2 for extended features

